description.narrative:
Danmission and the Danish Ministry of Foreign Affairs has agreed to a Strategic Partnership to promote democracy and human rights by:

Strengthening faith-based organisations and theological institutions to take social action based on the actual needs of the people they serve and thereby be catalysts for promotion and protection of human rights including freedom of Religion and Belief;   

Strengthening inclusive and just community building through interfaith and intercultural dialogue, peaceful coexistence and conflict management, and support democratic societies based on human rights and active citizenship;   

Strengthening civil society actors and faith-based actors through theological and spiritual reflections on resource scarcity and the interconnectedness between people and nature to engage actively in natural resource protection and management, empowering local com-munities  to  engage  actively  in  the  protection  and  management  of  natural  resources,  in  preventing  and  mitigating  natural  resource  conflicts,  and  in  accessing  natural  resources  and other income-generating opportunities
